properties.Name: ConsumerPaymentCardRelatedParty
properties.Description: A party that has a relationship to the Payment Card for the indicated period.

Columns.Name: PaymentCardId
Columns.Description:
Primary Account Number (PAN) = The number that is embossed, encoded, or both, on a plastic card that identifies the issuer and the particular cardholder account.

The account number on the card, which is unique to every cardholder. The card number is used to identify the purchaser for authorization and billing purposes.

Columns.Name: PartyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Party.

Columns.Name: PaymentCardPartyRelationshipTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a co-signer relationship.

Columns.Name: PaymentCardRelatedPartyNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the Payment Card Party Relationship.
